(530, 'Person familiar with deal tells AP that Sabres reach 5-year agreement to re-sign C Tyler Ennis', 'http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=726442', '\r\nBUFFALO, N.Y. - A person familiar with the agreement has confirmed to The Associated Press that the Buffalo Sabres have reached an agreement to re-sign centre Tyler Ennis to a five-year contract worth about $23 million.\r\n\r\nThe person spoke early...', 4, 1405573501, 'Thu, 17 Jul 2014 01:05:01 EDT', 0),
(531, 'Penguins'' Crosby wins Best NHL Player at ESPYs', 'http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=726483', 'Pittsburgh Penguins forward Sidney Crosby was named Best NHL Player at the 2014 ESPY Awards on Wednesday.\r\n\r\nCrosby, who led the League in scoring with 104 points last season, was given the Hart Trophy as NHL MVP in June.\r\n\r\nCrosby and New York Ra...', 4, 1405568400, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 23:40:00 EDT', 0),
(532, 'Defenseman Butler signs one-year contract with Blues', 'http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=726517', 'Defenseman Chris Butler signed a one-year, two-way contract with the St. Louis Blues, the team announced Wednesday. Financial terms were not disclosed.\r\n\r\n"My personal goal is to come to training camp and compete for a spot," Butler told the St. L...', 4, 1405566360, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 23:06:00 EDT', 0),
(533, 'Defensemen Demers, Doherty sign with Sharks', 'http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=726513', 'Defenseman Jason Demers and the San Jose Sharks agreed to terms Wednesday on a two-year contract. Financial terms were not released but the contract is worth $3.4 million per season, according to Elliotte Friedman of "Hockey Night In Canada."\r\n\r\n"...', 4, 1405566120, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 23:02:00 EDT', 0),
(534, 'Thompson joins Oilers as assistant coach', 'http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=726509', 'Rocky Thompson has been hired by the Edmonton Oilers as an assistant coach on Dallas Eakins'' staff.\r\n\r\nThompson, 36, had been an assistant coach for the past four seasons with the Oilers'' American Hockey League team, the Oklahoma City Barons. He s...', 4, 1405561140, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 21:39:00 EDT', 0),
(535, 'Rangers agree to terms with free-agent F Matthew Lombardi', 'http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=726441', '\r\nNEW YORK, N.Y. - The New York Rangers have agreed to terms with free agent forward Matthew Lombardi, a veteran NHL player who spent last season in Switzerland.\r\n\r\nThe 32-year-old Lombardi, who joined New York on Wednesday, had 20 goals and 30 as...', 4, 1405554301, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 19:45:01 EDT', 0),
(536, 'Official 2014 free agent signings tracker', 'http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=724642', 'NOTE: This is the official free agent signings list as of July 16 at 6:04 PM ET.\r\n\r\nDATE PLAYER 2014-15 TEAM PREVIOUS TEAM\r\n\r\nJULY 16 D Chris Butler St. Louis Calgary\r\nJULY 16 D Taylor Doherty San Jose San Jose\r\nJULY 16 D Jason Demers San Jose San...', 4, 1405548240, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 18:04:00 EDT', 0),
(537, 'Official 2014 list of available free agents', 'http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=724639', 'NOTE: Below is a list of players, who, effective July 1, became free agents. Players will be removed upon signing with a team.\r\n\r\nANAHEIM DUCKS\r\n\r\nGroup 2 FAs: Andre Petersson, Jakob Silfverberg, Devante Smith-Pelly, Sami Vatanen.\r\n\r\nGroup 3 UFAs:...', 4, 1405548180, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 18:03:00 EDT', 0),
(538, 'Penguins'' Crosby using treatment to avoid surgery', 'http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=726232', 'Pittsburgh Penguins center Sidney Crosby will not need surgery to repair an injury to his right wrist, the team said Tuesday.\r\n\r\nThe Penguins on July 9 said Crosby had been receiving treatment for a wrist injury he sustained last season and surger...', 4, 1405547820, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 17:57:00 EDT', 0),
(539, 'San Jose Sharks re-sign defencemen Jason Demers, Taylor Doherty', 'http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=726439', '\r\nSAN JOSE, Calif. - The San Jose Sharks have re-signed defencemen Jason Demers and Taylor Doherty.\r\n\r\nThe Sharks announced the agreements with both restricted free agents Wednesday. The team says Demers'' deal is for two years, while Doherty''s dea...', 4, 1405545301, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 17:15:01 EDT', 0),
(540, 'What to watch for in the second half', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/anthony-castrovince-what-to-watch-for-in-second-half-of-the-season?ymd=20140718&content_id=85070378&vkey=news_mlb', 'Today is our Opening Day, Part Deux, our return to normalcy, and here''s a list of some of the best things to look for in the second half of the season.', 1, 1405659853, 'Fri, 18 Jul 2014 01:04:13 EDT\n	', 0),
(541, 'Daniels: Club not rushing Holland''s recovery', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/jon-daniels-texas-rangers-not-rushing-derek-holland-recovery?ymd=20140718&content_id=85065858&vkey=news_mlb', 'If the Rangers weren''t struggling mightily this season, left-hander Derek Holland could have potentially returned to the club already. General manager Jon Daniels said Holland, who underwent left knee surgery in the offseason, is expected to rejoin the rotation by late August.', 1, 1405658727, 'Fri, 18 Jul 2014 00:45:27 EDT\n	', 0),
(542, 'Twins prospect Stewart in command at A ball', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/minnesota-twins-prospect-kohl-stewart-in-command-at-class-a?ymd=20140718&content_id=85063294&vkey=news_mlb', 'Right-hander Kohl Stewart, the Twins'' No. 4 prospect, threw five scoreless innings Thursday as Class A Cedar Rapids defeated Lake County. Stewart, ranked No. 32 on MLBPipeline.com''s Top 100 Prospects list, didn''t allow a runner to advance past second base in the win.', 1, 1405657054, 'Fri, 18 Jul 2014 00:17:34 EDT\n	', 0),
(543, 'Bryant pads MiLB lead as Cubs ''Big 3'' all homer', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/kris-bryant-pads-milb-lead-as-cubs-top-three-prospects-homer?ymd=20140717&content_id=85060658&vkey=news_mlb', 'Javier Baez, Kris Bryant and Addison Russell, the Cubs'' top three prospects, all homered Thursday. Bryant moved into first by himself with his 32nd in the Minors this season. He had been tied with Futures Game MVP Joey Gallo, the Rangers'' No. 2 prospect.', 1, 1405655570, 'Thu, 17 Jul 2014 23:52:50 EDT\n	', 0),
(544, 'In 20th big league season, Hawkins never better', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/terence-moore-latroy-hawkins-is-baseballs-ultimate-survivor?ymd=20140717&content_id=85057396&vkey=news_mlb', 'LaTroy Hawkins, 41, is among the game''s elite relievers this season despite operating in a little house of horrors for pitchers called Coors Field. He is on the verge of becoming just the 15th pitcher ever to appear in 1,000 games, and he has never been better. This only makes sense if you know about his difficult baseball journey.', 1, 1405655875, 'Thu, 17 Jul 2014 23:57:55 EDT\n	', 0),
(545, 'Diaz tosses six innings of three-hit ball at Class A', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/mariners-prospect-edwin-diaz-tosses-six-innings-at-class-a-clinton?ymd=20140717&content_id=85052424&vkey=news_mlb', 'Right-hander Edwin Diaz, the Mariners'' No. 4 prospect, threw six scoreless innings Thursday as Class A Clinton shut out Great Lakes, 5-0. He struck out eight batters and faced just two hitters above the minimum.', 1, 1405651830, 'Thu, 17 Jul 2014 22:50:30 EDT\n	', 0),
(546, 'Gattis pleased with first test in Triple-A rehab', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/evan-gattis-pleased-with-first-test-in-triple-a-rehab-for-back-injury?ymd=20140717&content_id=85047684&vkey=news_mlb', 'Braves catcher Evan Gattis played the first game of his rehab assignment with Triple-A Gwinnett pain-free on Thursday night. He went 0-for-4 as he works to regain his timing after an absence of nearly three weeks.', 1, 1405649429, 'Thu, 17 Jul 2014 22:10:29 EDT\n	', 0),
(547, 'Twin bill forces Tribe to get creative with rotation', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20140717&content_id=85046262&notebook_id=85046390&vkey=notebook_cle&c_id=cle', 'The Indians'' front office is always trying to find creative ways to get the most out of the team''s roster. With only three active starting pitchers to begin the second half, Cleveland is at it again, calling up Zach McAllister for Saturday''s twin bill in Detroit, then T.J. House for Monday''s opener in Minnesota.', 1, 1405647251, 'Thu, 17 Jul 2014 21:34:11 EDT\n	', 0),
(548, 'Masterson pleased with progress but needs more time', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20140717&content_id=85046262&notebook_id=85046026&vkey=notebook_cle&c_id=cle', 'Justin Masterson may not have wanted to go on the disabled list, but the Indians'' sinkerballer is willing to accept that it was the right decision for the team. While sidelined, the pitcher has worked diligently on both his delivery and his recovery.', 1, 1405647040, 'Thu, 17 Jul 2014 21:30:40 EDT\n	', 0);
